---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="SessionFS — The AI memory layer for coding agents" description="The AI memory layer for coding agents. Capture, resume, and hand off AI coding sessions across Claude Code, Codex, Cursor, Gemini, and more.">


  <!-- ========== 1. HERO ========== -->
  <section class="relative pt-32 sm:pt-40 pb-20 sm:pb-28 px-5 noise">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto flex flex-col lg:flex-row items-center gap-12 lg:gap-8">
      <!-- Left 60% -->
      <div class="lg:w-[58%] text-center lg:text-left">
        <div class="fade-up mb-6">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 64 64" class="h-12 w-12 mx-auto lg:mx-0" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <path d="M20,10 Q8,10 8,22 L8,42 Q8,54 20,54" fill="none" stroke="#4f9cf7" stroke-width="4" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <path d="M44,10 Q56,10 56,22 L56,42 Q56,54 44,54" fill="none" stroke="#3ddc84" stroke-width="4" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <circle cx="32" cy="32" r="7" fill="#4f9cf7"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h1 class="fade-up font-heading text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-extrabold tracking-tight leading-[1.1] mb-6">
          The AI memory layer<br>for coding agents.
        </h1>
        <p class="fade-up text-lg sm:text-xl text-muted leading-relaxed max-w-xl mx-auto lg:mx-0 mb-8">
          Capture every AI coding session, resume it in another tool, hand it to a teammate or agent, and turn the work into shared memory, rules, tickets, and audit.
        </p>
        <div class="fade-up inline-flex items-center gap-3 bg-surface border border-border rounded-lg px-5 py-3 mb-8 font-mono text-sm">
          <span class="text-muted-dim select-none">$</span>
          <span class="text-accent">pip install sessionfs</span>
          <button onclick="copyText('pip install sessionfs', this)" class="text-muted-dim hover:text-brand text-[13px] border border-border rounded px-2.5 py-0.5 ml-1 transition-colors">Copy</button>
        </div>
        <div class="fade-up flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3 justify-center lg:justify-start">
          <a href="https://app.sessionfs.dev/login?mode=signup" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 bg-brand text-white font-semibold rounded-lg px-7 py-3 hover:brightness-110 transition">
            Sign up for cloud
            <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6"/></svg>
          </a>
          <a href="/quickstart/" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 border border-border text-txt font-semibold rounded-lg px-7 py-3 hover:border-muted transition">
            Read quickstart
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- Right 40% terminal -->
      <div class="lg:w-[42%] w-full relative fade-up">
        <div class="hero-glow"></div>
        <div class="term relative z-10">
          <div class="term-bar">
            <div class="term-dot bg-[#ff5f57]"></div>
            <div class="term-dot bg-[#febc2e]"></div>
            <div class="term-dot bg-[#28c840]"></div>
            <span class="ml-3 text-muted-dim text-[13px] font-mono">~/ terminal</span>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 sm:p-5 font-mono text-sm leading-relaxed overflow-x-auto">
            <div class="text-muted-dim">$ <span class="text-accent">sfs list --today</span></div>
            <div class="mt-3 text-muted"><span class="text-brand">ses_a1b2</span> Claude Code&nbsp; "Debug auth middleware"&nbsp; 47 msgs</div>
            <div class="text-muted"><span class="text-brand">ses_c3d4</span> Codex&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "Refactor schema"&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 31 msgs</div>
            <div class="border-t border-border mt-3 pt-3 space-y-1">
              <div class="text-muted-dim">$ <span class="text-accent">sfs resume ses_a1b2 --in codex</span></div>
              <div class="text-muted"><span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span> Transcript converted for Codex</div>
              <div class="text-muted"><span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span> Workspace + git snapshot attached</div>
              <div class="text-muted"><span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span> Rules synced to codex.md</div>
            </div>
            <div class="border-t border-border mt-3 pt-3">
              <div class="text-muted-dim">$ <span class="text-accent">sfs handoff ses_a1b2 --to sarah@company.dev</span></div>
              <div class="text-accent mt-1">Secure handoff created.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========== 2. SOCIAL PROOF BAR ========== -->
  <div class="grad-divider"></div>
  <section class="py-8 px-5 fade-up">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto flex flex-col gap-3 text-sm items-center">
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-3 sm:gap-5">
        <span class="text-muted-dim font-medium shrink-0">Local tools</span>
        <div class="border-l border-border h-4 hidden sm:block"></div>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-x-5 gap-y-2 font-mono text-muted text-sm">
          <span>Claude Code</span><span>Codex</span><span>Gemini</span><span>Copilot</span><span>Cursor</span><span>Amp</span><span>Cline</span><span>Roo Code</span><span>Kilo Code</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-3 sm:gap-5">
        <span class="text-muted-dim font-medium shrink-0">Cloud-agent-ready</span>
        <div class="border-l border-border h-4 hidden sm:block"></div>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-x-5 gap-y-2 font-mono text-muted text-sm">
          <span>AWS Bedrock</span><span>Google Vertex</span><span>Custom API clients</span>
        </div>
        <span class="text-muted-dim text-xs">(via integration docs)</span>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-3 sm:gap-5">
        <img src="https://img.shields.io/github/stars/SessionFS/sessionfs?style=flat&color=30363d&labelColor=161b22&logo=github&logoColor=e6edf3" alt="GitHub stars" class="h-5 shrink-0">
        <div class="border-l border-border h-4 hidden sm:block"></div>
        <span class="font-mono text-muted text-sm">2,007 backend + 187 UI tests</span>
        <span class="text-muted-dim text-sm">Enterprise-tested in healthcare on AWS EKS</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <div class="grad-divider"></div>

  <!-- ========== 3. THREE PILLARS ========== -->
  <section class="relative py-20 sm:py-28 px-5 noise">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-5">

        <!-- Memory -->
        <a href="/features/knowledge-base/" class="glass fade-up p-6 block group" style="border-top: 3px solid #4f9cf7;">
          <div class="mb-4">
            <div class="text-sm font-mono text-brand uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Memory</div>
            <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-xl mb-3 group-hover:text-brand transition-colors">Agents remember what the team learned.</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="text-muted text-base leading-relaxed mb-4">Every captured session becomes durable knowledge: decisions, patterns, project context, wiki pages, rules provenance, and agent write-back built from inspectable evidence.</p>
          <div class="font-mono text-sm text-brand">Learn more &rarr;</div>
        </a>

        <!-- Portability -->
        <a href="/features/" class="glass fade-up p-6 block group" style="border-top: 3px solid #3ddc84;">
          <div class="mb-4">
            <div class="text-sm font-mono text-accent uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Portability</div>
            <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-xl mb-3 group-hover:text-brand transition-colors">Capture once. Resume anywhere.</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="text-muted text-base leading-relaxed mb-4">SessionFS captures AI coding sessions from 9 tools into a portable <span class="font-mono text-txt">.sfs</span> record. Switch machines, switch tools, or come back tomorrow without rebuilding context.</p>
          <div class="font-mono text-sm text-accent">Learn more &rarr;</div>
        </a>

        <!-- Handoff -->
        <a href="/features/handoff/" class="glass fade-up p-6 block group" style="border-top: 3px solid #4f9cf7;">
          <div class="mb-4">
            <div class="text-sm font-mono text-brand uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Handoff</div>
            <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-xl mb-3 group-hover:text-brand transition-colors">Move work with full context</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="text-muted text-base leading-relaxed mb-4">Send a session to a teammate, another machine, or an agent persona. The recipient gets the conversation, files, git state, rules, ticket, and provenance instead of a pasted summary.</p>
          <div class="font-mono text-sm text-brand">Learn more &rarr;</div>
        </a>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Governance Layer -->
  <section class="relative py-14 px-5">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="fade-up text-sm font-mono text-muted-dim uppercase tracking-wider text-center mb-6">Enterprise governance, built in</div>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6 text-center">
        <a href="/features/judge/" class="fade-up block hover:opacity-80 transition">
          <div class="text-xl font-bold text-txt mb-1">LLM Judge</div>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">Cross-references every AI claim against tool output. Contradictions surface before they reach production.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/enterprise/" class="fade-up block hover:opacity-80 transition">
          <div class="text-xl font-bold text-txt mb-1">DLP &amp; Secrets</div>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">14 PHI patterns + 19 secret patterns scrub session archives at the server. BLOCK / REDACT / WARN modes.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/features/handoff/" class="fade-up block hover:opacity-80 transition">
          <div class="text-xl font-bold text-txt mb-1">Audit Trail</div>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">Every captured session carries instruction provenance, persona, ticket, and the AgentRun that signed off.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/self-hosted/" class="fade-up block hover:opacity-80 transition">
          <div class="text-xl font-bold text-txt mb-1">Self-hosted Helm</div>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">Hardened chart (UID 10001, read-only rootfs, RuntimeDefault seccomp). Your data stays in your cluster.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="grad-divider"></div>

  <!-- ========== 4. KNOWLEDGE BASE SPOTLIGHT (flagship) ========== -->
  <section class="relative py-20 sm:py-28 px-5 bg-surface/50 noise">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto flex flex-col lg:flex-row items-center gap-12">
      <div class="lg:w-1/2 fade-up">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold mb-5">Memory starts with a portable session.</h2>
        <p class="text-muted text-lg mb-4 leading-relaxed">SessionFS captures the raw evidence first: transcript, tool, workspace state, git snapshot, rules, persona, and ticket provenance. That portable record is what makes resume, handoff, audit, and memory reliable.</p>
        <p class="text-muted text-lg mb-4 leading-relaxed">Then every captured session is distilled into knowledge entries — architecture decisions, debugging patterns, API contracts, and environment quirks. Your codebase builds its own documentation over time.</p>
        <p class="text-muted text-lg mb-6 leading-relaxed">AI agents don't just read the knowledge base — they write back. When an agent discovers something new during a session, it adds the finding automatically via MCP. The next agent picks it up.</p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-6">
          <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 bg-surface border border-border rounded-full px-3 py-1 text-sm font-mono text-muted">58 MCP tools</span>
          <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 bg-surface border border-border rounded-full px-3 py-1 text-sm font-mono text-muted">Auto-compiled wiki</span>
          <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 bg-surface border border-border rounded-full px-3 py-1 text-sm font-mono text-muted">Agent write-back</span>
        </div>
        <a href="/features/knowledge-base/" class="text-brand hover:underline text-sm font-medium">Learn more &rarr;</a>
      </div>
      <div class="lg:w-1/2 w-full fade-up">
        <div class="term">
          <div class="term-bar"><div class="term-dot bg-[#ff5f57]"></div><div class="term-dot bg-[#febc2e]"></div><div class="term-dot bg-[#28c840]"></div><span class="ml-3 text-muted-dim text-[13px] font-mono">knowledge base</span></div>
          <div class="p-5 font-mono text-sm space-y-3">
            <div><span class="text-muted-dim">$</span> <span class="text-accent">sfs project ask "How does auth work?"</span></div>
            <div class="mt-3 border-t border-border pt-3">
              <div class="text-muted-dim uppercase text-[11px] tracking-wider mb-2">Knowledge Base Results</div>
              <div class="text-muted text-sm mb-2"><span class="text-brand">auth/middleware</span> — JWT validation via PyJWT. Tokens refreshed on 401. Middleware checks Authorization header, decodes with RS256.</div>
              <div class="text-muted text-sm mb-2"><span class="text-brand">auth/oauth2</span> — OAuth2 flow uses authorization_code grant. Callback at /auth/callback. Tokens stored in httponly cookies.</div>
              <div class="text-muted text-sm"><span class="text-brand">auth/testing</span> — Test fixtures use factory_boy. Auth tokens mocked via conftest.py pytest fixtures.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="border-t border-border pt-3">
              <div class="text-accent text-sm">Answer saved to knowledge base. &#10003;</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="grad-divider"></div>

  <!-- ========== 5. LLM JUDGE SPOTLIGHT ========== -->
  <section class="relative py-20 sm:py-28 px-5 noise">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto flex flex-col lg:flex-row items-center gap-12">
      <div class="lg:w-1/2 fade-up">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold mb-5">Reviewable AI at scale.</h2>
        <p class="text-muted text-lg mb-4 leading-relaxed">Every AI coding agent makes claims: "the test passes," "I created the file," "the migration is safe." Most go unverified. LLM Judge cross-references every claim against actual evidence — exit codes, file writes, test output.</p>
        <p class="text-muted text-lg mb-4 leading-relaxed">Confidence-scored findings surface on PRs and in the dashboard. Your team reviews AI work the same way they review human work.</p>
        <p class="text-muted text-base mb-6 leading-relaxed">Verified claims feed the knowledge base — building a trust record your team can reference.</p>
        <p class="text-base text-muted-dim border-l-2 border-brand/30 pl-4 mb-6 leading-relaxed">BYOK — your key, never stored. Works with any OpenAI-compatible endpoint: OpenRouter, LiteLLM, vLLM, Ollama.</p>
        <a href="/features/judge/" class="text-brand hover:underline text-sm font-medium">Read the docs &rarr;</a>
      </div>
      <div class="lg:w-1/2 w-full fade-up">
        <div class="term">
          <div class="term-bar"><div class="term-dot bg-[#ff5f57]"></div><div class="term-dot bg-[#febc2e]"></div><div class="term-dot bg-[#28c840]"></div><span class="ml-3 text-muted-dim text-[13px] font-mono">audit report</span></div>
          <div class="p-5 font-mono text-sm space-y-4">
            <div>
              <div class="text-muted-dim uppercase tracking-wider text-sm mb-2">Trust Score</div>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
                <span class="text-xl font-bold text-warning">74%</span>
                <div class="flex-1 h-2 bg-border rounded-full overflow-hidden"><div class="h-full bg-warning rounded-full w-[74%]"></div></div>
              </div>
              <div class="text-sm"><span class="text-danger">3 contradictions</span> <span class="text-muted-dim">&middot;</span> <span class="text-warning">9 unverified</span> <span class="text-muted-dim">&middot;</span> <span class="text-accent">42 verified</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="border-t border-border pt-4 space-y-3">
              <div class="bg-danger/5 rounded-lg p-3 border border-danger/20">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                  <span class="bg-danger/15 text-danger text-[11px] font-bold px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">CRITICAL</span>
                  <span class="bg-bg/50 text-muted-dim text-[11px] px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">test_result</span>
                </div>
                <div class="text-muted text-sm mb-1">AI: "The test passes successfully"</div>
                <div class="bg-bg/60 rounded px-2 py-1.5 text-[12px] text-danger/80 mt-1">FAILED tests/test_auth.py<br>assert status_code == 200, got 401<br>exit code: 1</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-warning/5 rounded-lg p-3 border border-warning/20">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                  <span class="bg-warning/15 text-warning text-[11px] font-bold px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">HIGH</span>
                  <span class="bg-bg/50 text-muted-dim text-[11px] px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">file_existence</span>
                </div>
                <div class="text-muted text-sm">AI: "I've created validator.py"</div>
                <div class="text-muted-dim text-[12px] mt-1">Reality: No Write call to that path</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="grad-divider"></div>

  <!-- ========== 6. HOW IT WORKS ========== -->
  <section class="relative py-20 sm:py-28 px-5 bg-surface/50 noise">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="fade-up font-heading text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-4">From session to governed workflow</h2>
      <p class="fade-up text-muted text-center mb-14 max-w-xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">SessionFS starts with capture, then turns that work into reusable context, assigned tasks, and auditable agent runs.</p>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <!-- Step 1 -->
        <div class="fade-up">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-5">
            <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-9 h-9 rounded-full bg-brand/10 text-brand text-sm font-bold border border-brand/20">1</span>
            <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-lg">Capture the work</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="term text-sm">
            <div class="term-bar"><div class="term-dot bg-[#ff5f57]"></div><div class="term-dot bg-[#febc2e]"></div><div class="term-dot bg-[#28c840]"></div></div>
            <div class="p-4 font-mono">
              <div><span class="text-muted-dim">$</span> <span class="text-accent">sfs daemon start</span></div>
              <div class="text-muted mt-2">Watching 9 tools... (PID 48201)</div>
              <div class="text-muted">claude-code <span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span> codex <span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span> gemini <span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span></div>
              <div class="text-muted">copilot <span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span> cursor <span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span> amp <span class="text-accent">&#10003;</span></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-muted text-base mt-4 leading-relaxed">Sessions are captured from 9 tools automatically. The raw work becomes the evidence trail.</p>
        </div>
        <!-- Step 2 -->
        <div class="fade-up">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-5">
            <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-9 h-9 rounded-full bg-brand/10 text-brand text-sm font-bold border border-brand/20">2</span>
            <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-lg">Load shared context</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="term text-sm">
            <div class="term-bar"><div class="term-dot bg-[#ff5f57]"></div><div class="term-dot bg-[#febc2e]"></div><div class="term-dot bg-[#28c840]"></div></div>
            <div class="p-4 font-mono">
              <div><span class="text-muted-dim">$</span> <span class="text-accent">sfs ticket start tk_184</span></div>
              <div class="text-muted mt-2">Loading persona: Atlas</div>
              <div class="text-muted">KB claims: 6 relevant</div>
              <div class="text-accent">Rules + criteria ready.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-muted text-base mt-4 leading-relaxed">The agent receives the right persona, project knowledge, rules, file refs, and acceptance criteria before it starts.</p>
        </div>
        <!-- Step 3 -->
        <div class="fade-up">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-5">
            <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-9 h-9 rounded-full bg-brand/10 text-brand text-sm font-bold border border-brand/20">3</span>
            <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-lg">Enforce the outcome</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="term text-sm">
            <div class="term-bar"><div class="term-dot bg-[#ff5f57]"></div><div class="term-dot bg-[#febc2e]"></div><div class="term-dot bg-[#28c840]"></div></div>
            <div class="p-4 font-mono">
              <div><span class="text-muted-dim">$</span> <span class="text-accent">sfs agent run codex-reviewer --fail-on high</span></div>
              <div class="text-muted mt-2">Reviewing PR #184...</div>
              <div class="text-accent mt-1">PASSED — medium severity</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-muted text-base mt-4 leading-relaxed">AgentRuns record severity, findings, policy result, and exit code so CI and humans can trust the result.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="grad-divider"></div>

  <!-- ========== 7. FEATURE GRID (6 cards) ========== -->
  <section class="relative py-20 sm:py-28 px-5 noise">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="fade-up font-heading text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-14">Everything you need</h2>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-5">
        <!-- AgentRun + CI -->
        <div class="glass p-6 fade-up" style="border-color: rgba(79,156,247,0.45);">
          <div class="mb-3 flex items-center gap-2"><svg class="w-7 h-7" fill="none" stroke="#4f9cf7" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12.75L11.25 15 15 9.75M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/></svg></div>
          <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-base mb-2">AgentRun + CI Integration</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-base mb-3 leading-relaxed">An auditable execution record for one persona run &mdash; CI-friendly policy enforcement with severity &times; <span class="font-mono">fail_on</span> &rarr; <span class="font-mono">exit_code</span>. Tracking + enforcement, not model auto-spawning. GitHub Actions + GitLab CI workflows shipped.</p>
          <div class="font-mono text-sm text-accent bg-bg/50 rounded-md p-2.5">sfs agent run --persona shield-sr</div>
        </div>
        <!-- Personas + Tickets (v0.10.1) -->
        <div class="glass p-6 fade-up">
